Columns: 262;
                                                  ruled lines: 42;
                                                  written lines: 42; Uniform layout. Ruling by hard point.Visible stitching. 262 columns in total, one to five columns per membrane. The second דרש of Lev. 10:16 is not placed at the beginning of the line. Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהיק, the letter ח is occasionally arched.  Several instances of majuscular and minuscular letters. Special shapes of the letter  נ, פ and broken ו occur. The "puncta extraordinaria" placed on the words fixed by masorah, except Gen. 16:5. Wooden rollers (currently kept in a separate box).
